# Prepare data for XGBoost (train/test datasets, lags, and other features)

  mutate(lag_1 = lag(`Total Primary Energy Consumption`, 1),
         lag_2 = lag(`Total Primary Energy Consumption`, 2)) %>%
  drop_na()

  mutate(lag_1 = lag(`Total Primary Energy Consumption`, 1),

  drop_na()

                         label = train_xgb$`Total Primary Energy Consumption`)

xgb_test <- xgb.DMatrix(data = as.matrix(test_xgb[, c("lag_1", "lag_2")]))

# Train the XGBoost model
xgb_model <- xgboost(data = xgb_train, nrounds = 100, objective = "reg:squarederror")

# XGBoost Forecasting
xgb_forecast <- predict(xgb_model, newdata = xgb_test)

# Combine the forecasts using weighted averaging (you can adjust the weights)
weights <- c(0.4, 0.4, 0.2)  # Example weights for ARIMA, ETS, XGBoost

# Align all forecasts with the test set (to ensure equal length)
combined_forecasts <- data.frame(
  Date = test$Month[1:12],  # Take the first 12 months of test set
  ARIMA_Forecast = forecast_arima$.mean[1:12],  # Ensure the forecasted values are aligned
  ETS_Forecast = forecast_ets$.mean[1:12],  # Ensure the forecasted values are aligned
  XGBoost_Forecast = xgb_forecast[1:12]  # Ensure the forecasted values are aligned
)

# Calculate hybrid forecast by weighted average
combined_forecasts$Hybrid_Forecast <- 
  weights[1] * combined_forecasts$ARIMA_Forecast + 
  weights[2] * combined_forecasts$ETS_Forecast + 
  weights[3] * combined_forecasts$XGBoost_Forecast



combined_forecasts %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -Date, names_to = "Model", values_to = "Forecast") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Date, y = Forecast, color = Model)) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Combined Forecasts",
       x = "Date", y = "Forecasted Energy Consumption")

# Task 8: Accuracy measures for all models

# Define metric functions
rmse <- function(actual, predicted) {
  sqrt(mean((actual - predicted)^2, na.rm = TRUE))
}

mae <- function(actual, predicted) {
  mean(abs(actual - predicted), na.rm = TRUE)
}

mse <- function(actual, predicted) {
  mean((actual - predicted)^2, na.rm = TRUE)
}

mape <- function(actual, predicted) {
  mean(abs((actual - predicted) / actual), na.rm = TRUE) * 100
}

# R-squared function
r_squared <- function(actual, predicted) {
  1 - (sum((actual - predicted)^2, na.rm = TRUE) / sum((actual - mean(actual, na.rm = TRUE))^2, na.rm = TRUE))
}

# Evaluation metrics function
eval_metrics <- function(actual, forecast) {
  rmse_val <- rmse(actual, forecast)
  mae_val <- mae(actual, forecast)
  mse_val <- mse(actual, forecast)
  mape_val <- mape(actual, forecast)
  r2_val <- r_squared(actual, forecast)
  return(c(RMSE = rmse_val, MAE = mae_val, MSE = mse_val, MAPE = mape_val, R2 = r2_val))
}

# Calculate metrics for ARIMA model
metrics_arima <- eval_metrics(
  test$`Total Primary Energy Consumption`[1:12],
  combined_forecasts$ARIMA_Forecast
)

# Calculate metrics for ETS model
metrics_ets <- eval_metrics(
  test$`Total Primary Energy Consumption`[1:12],
  combined_forecasts$ETS_Forecast
)

# Calculate metrics for XGBoost model
metrics_xgb <- eval_metrics(
  test$`Total Primary Energy Consumption`[1:12],
  combined_forecasts$XGBoost_Forecast
)

# Calculate metrics for Hybrid model
metrics_hybrid <- eval_metrics(
  test$`Total Primary Energy Consumption`[1:12],
  combined_forecasts$Hybrid_Forecast
)

# Combine all metrics into a data frame
all_metrics <- data.frame(
  Model = c("ARIMA", "ETS", "XGBoost", "Hybrid"),
  RMSE = c(metrics_arima["RMSE"], metrics_ets["RMSE"], metrics_xgb["RMSE"], metrics_hybrid["RMSE"]),
  MAE = c(metrics_arima["MAE"], metrics_ets["MAE"], metrics_xgb["MAE"], metrics_hybrid["MAE"]),
  MSE = c(metrics_arima["MSE"], metrics_ets["MSE"], metrics_xgb["MSE"], metrics_hybrid["MSE"]),
  MAPE = c(metrics_arima["MAPE"], metrics_ets["MAPE"], metrics_xgb["MAPE"], metrics_hybrid["MAPE"]),
  R2 = c(metrics_arima["R2"], metrics_ets["R2"], metrics_xgb["R2"], metrics_hybrid["R2"])
)

# Display the metrics
print(all_metrics)
